line.token: 'Minimum severity the driver will log. Follows Psr LogLevel. Default is "error".'
'The default driver to use. Default is the first configured driver.'
'List of drivers to use. If no drivers are configured the default driver will try to open a bolt connection without authentication on localhost over port 7687'
'The alias for this driver. Default is "default".'
'Enable profiling for requests on this driver. If no value is provided the default value will be equal to the kernel.debug parameter.'
'The DSN for the driver. Default is "bolt://localhost:7687".'
'The priority of this when trying to fall back on the same alias. Default is 0'
'The amount of rows that are being fetched at once in the result cursor'
'The default access mode for every session. Default is WRITE.'
'Select the standard database to use. Default is value is null, meaning the preconfigured database by the server is used (usually a database called neo4j).'
'The default timeout for acquiring a connection from the connection pool. Default is %s seconds. Note that this is different from the transaction timeout.'
'The default user agent this driver. Default is "neo4j-php-client/%client-version-numer%".'
'The default maximum number of connections in the connection pool. Default is %s. Connections are lazily created and closed.'
'Verify the peer certificate. Default is true.'
'The default transaction timeout. If null is provided it will fall back tot he preconfigured timeout on the server'
